flowRoot.flowPara: researchers develop new software tools to solve existing bioinformatics problems
these tools and their benefits are described in manuscripts and published as journal articles
biologists with a bioinformatics problem have to search the eixsting literature to find the tools they need
published software however may no longer exist or the developer has moved on
even if the software is available it may be difficult to install
the software may be hard to use and good results may require experience
researchers develop new software tools to solve existing bioinformatics problems
the developer creates a Docker container for the tool and includes all dependencies required to run it
bioboxes.org lists available bioboxes for common bioinformatics tasks, these bioboxes can be downloaded
bioboxes have a simplified comand line interface allowing a biologist to more easily process their data
the same biobox types have the same interface allowing one to be swapped for another
